"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444912","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-19","<p>The preliminary feedback to which my earlier answer refers is the outcome of private informal conversations that the Green Investment Bank (GIB) and our financial advisers have had with a number of potential investors on an in‑confidence basis to help gauge market appetite for acquiring a stake in GIB. The substance of these conversations is commercially sensitive and not for publication. The Government does, though, intend to report to Parliament setting out our detailed plans for a sale and to provide a further report following completion of a transaction and any subsequent transactions.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-01-19T16:15:01.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444912/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444912/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444912/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-14","Green Investment Bank: Privatisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Answer of 30 November 2015 to Question 14108, if he will place in the Library a copy of the preliminary feedback on his announcement of the privatisation of the Green Investment Bank.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","22689"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444913","Cabinet Office","false","2016-02-01","<p>In due course.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-02-01T16:56:07.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444913/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444913/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444913/answer","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444913/answer/previousversion/39977","Biography information for Matt Hancock","53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-01-14","Foreign Companies: Property","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, when the Government plans to launch its planned consultation on increasing the transparency of property ownership by foreign companies.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","22662"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444914","Cabinet Office","false","2016-01-21","<p>This information is not held centrally. Each employing department operates their own attendance management process and keep their own records.</p><p>The Civil Service strives to improve health and wellbeing at work for our staff and this remains a priority. We have reduced our level of sickness absence over the past five years and continue to actively manage our progress against benchmarking information. However if an employee does not meet the attendance level expected of them then we will take appropriate action, which in some cases might lead to dismissal.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-01-21T14:36:27.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444914/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444914/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444914/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-01-14","Civil Servants: Termination of Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the change in the number of civil servants who have had their employment terminated due to absence related to their sickness record has been in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","22680"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444916","Cabinet Office","false","2016-01-20","<p>In the spending review the Chancellor announced £80m for a new social outcomes fund to support the creation of locally developed social impact bonds tackling a range of social problems. The Cabinet Office has responsibility for the fund. The detailed criteria for the fund is being developed, but it will provide a portion of outcome payments for locally commissioned social impact bonds where some of the benefits and savings generated fall to central government.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson","22530","2016-01-20T16:04:02.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444916/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444916/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444916/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-01-14","Social Outcomes Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, which government department will have responsibility for the management of the social investment outcomes fund.","false","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr   Poulter","22545"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444917","Cabinet Office","false","2016-01-20","<p>One defibrillator has been provided in each of three buildings managed by the Cabinet Office. The buildings are: 10 Downing Street; Rosebery Court, Norwich; and Emergency Planning College, York.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","22566","2016-01-20T13:47:35.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444917/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444917/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444917/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-01-14","Cabinet Office: Defibrillators","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many defibrillators are provided in each building his Department manages.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","22551"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444918","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-03","<p>The number of requests for mandatory reconsideration of a decision about a tax credits award that Concentrix have received since the commencement of their contract with HM Revenue and Customs in November 2014 is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Month</p></td><td><p>Number of MRs</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>November 2014</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>December 2014</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January 2015</p></td><td><p>6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>February 2015</p></td><td><p>38</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>March 2015</p></td><td><p>29</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2015</p></td><td><p>137</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>May 2015</p></td><td><p>100</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>June 2015</p></td><td><p>45</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>July 2015</p></td><td><p>71</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>August 2015</p></td><td><p>108</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>September 2015</p></td><td><p>1221</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>October 2015</p></td><td><p>925</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>November 2015</p></td><td><p>871</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>December 2015</p></td><td><p>2371</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The total is about 1.6% of all decisions Concentrix made in the same period.</p><p> </p><p>As of 15 January 2016, there are 566 mandatory reconsiderations in progress that have been opened and Concentrix are waiting for customers to provide further evidence. Concentrix have 30 further mandatory reconsiderations that are awaiting determination.</p><p> </p><p>The average length of time taken between Concentrix starting to work a mandatory reconsideration and making a decision is 24 days. This includes the time needed for customers to provide any further evidence.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","22658 ; 22668","2016-02-03T09:57:24.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444918/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444918/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444918/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-14","Welfare Tax Credits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many applications for mandatory reconsideration of a tax credits decision have been made to Concentrix in each month since April 2014.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","22572"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444919","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-22","<p>HM Treasury manages 1 Horse Guard’s Road in which 6 defibrillators are located. On 29<sup>th</sup> September 2015, 1 Horse Guard’s Road received Automated External Defibrillator Accreditation by the London Ambulance Service.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-01-22T12:39:44.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444919/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444919/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444919/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-14","Treasury: Defibrillators","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many defibrillators are provided in each building his Department manages.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","22569"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444920","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-20","<p>EU VAT rules do not currently allow for the application of a zero rate of VAT to sanitary products. That is why I have written to the European Commission and other Member States setting out our strong view that Member States should have full discretion over what rate of VAT they can apply to these products.</p><br /><p>Drugs and medications that are dispensed by a registered pharmacist against a prescription issued by a qualifying health professional are zero rated for VAT.</p><br /><p>High-factor sunscreen is on the NHS prescription list for certain conditions and is therefore provided VAT free when dispensed by a pharmacist to patients.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-01-20T10:39:10.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444920/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444920/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444920/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-14","Sunscreens: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will include the removal of VAT on sun safety products in his negotiations on VAT on sanitary products with his counterparts in the EU.","false","Biography information for Mrs Pauline Latham","Mid Derbyshire","Pauline Latham","22538"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444921","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-20","<p>EU VAT law does not specifically provide for a reduced rate for sunscreen, although there is a provision for a reduced rate of VAT for “pharmaceutical products of a kind normally used for health care, prevention of diseases and treatment for medical and veterinary purposes”.</p><br /><p>Not all sunscreen products are recognised as having a health benefit and the factor level necessary for adequate protection is a matter of contention.</p><br /><p>However, high-factor sunscreen is on the NHS prescription list for certain conditions and provided VAT free when dispensed by a pharmacist to patients.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-01-20T10:23:54.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444921/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444921/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444921/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-14","Sunscreens: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will assess the potential merits of reducing the rate of VAT on sunscreen, sun block and other sun safety products.","false","Biography information for Mrs Pauline Latham","Mid Derbyshire","Pauline Latham","22539"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444922","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-20","<p>Information for (a) 2015-16 and (b) 2014-15 is not available. HMRC will be publishing the 2014-15 Tax Credits Finalised Awards National Statistics on 27th May 2016.</p><p>Information for 2013-14 can be found in the latest publication, Child and Working Tax Credits statistics, finalised annual awards - geographical analysis, which is available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-tax-credits-finalised-award-statistics-geographical-statistics-2013-to-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-tax-credits-finalised-award-statistics-geographical-statistics-2013-to-2014</a></p><p>Table 3 provides information on the average number of families in receipt of Child Tax Credit and/or Working Tax Credit and their average annual entitlements. For families in receipt of CTC and WTC, the average annual entitlement is the combined amount of both tax credits. The information is available for each Westminster Parliamentary constituency, including Bolton North East.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2016-01-20T16:23:21.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444922/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444922/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444922/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-14","Working Tax Credit: Bolton North East","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much has been paid in working tax credit to people in Bolton North East constituency in (a) 2015-16 to date, (b) 2014-15 and (c) 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Sir David Crausby","Bolton North East","Mr David Crausby","22524"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444923","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-21","<p>The proceeds obtained from government asset sales that are listed for the financial years 2010-15 can be obtained from the “Summer Budget 2015 data sources”, p20, which is available here, <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/443273/Data_sources_-_Summer_Budget_2015.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/443273/Data_sources_-_Summer_Budget_2015.pdf</a></p><br /><p>Announcements are available on gov.uk for sales since Summer Budget 2015 of RBS, Royal Mail, former Northern Rock mortgages and further sales of Lloyds Banking Group shares.</p><br />","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-01-21T11:42:17.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444923/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444923/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444923/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-14","Privatisation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what government assets and services have been privatised in each year since 2010; what the pre-sale valuation was of each such asset or service; and what income was generated by each such privatisation.","false","Biography information for Anne McLaughlin","Glasgow North East","Anne McLaughlin","22513"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444924","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-26","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) does not routinely publish this information.</p><br /><p>The Government recognises the importance to businesses of receiving VAT repayments as quickly as possible. HMRC also has a duty to ensure that incorrect or fraudulent repayments are identified and prevented. All repayment claims are subject to automated risk analysis on receipt and 94% are processed for immediate payment. Of the remainder, 50% are approved for payment within 5 days. Repayment Supplement is designed to compensate customers where HMRC fails to make a repayment within 30 days. In 2014-15, HMRC paid Repayment Supplement in 0.3% of all cases.</p><br /><p>In the first half of 2015-16, HMRC carried out an extensive review of its repayment process with a view to minimising delays in cases where repayments are not authorised automatically. Following the review, new processes have been introduced and HMRC expects to reduce the incidence of Repayment Supplement as a result.</p><br />","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-01-26T14:55:58.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444924/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444924/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444924/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-14","VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much HM Revenue and Customs has paid out in supplements following late payment of VAT returns in (a) 2015-16 and (b) each of the previous 10 years; and what steps his Department is taking to reduce that amount.","false","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse","22515"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444925","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-03","<p>The number of requests for mandatory reconsideration of a decision about a tax credits award that Concentrix have received since the commencement of their contract with HM Revenue and Customs in November 2014 is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Month</p></td><td><p>Number of MRs</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>November 2014</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>December 2014</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January 2015</p></td><td><p>6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>February 2015</p></td><td><p>38</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>March 2015</p></td><td><p>29</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2015</p></td><td><p>137</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>May 2015</p></td><td><p>100</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>June 2015</p></td><td><p>45</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>July 2015</p></td><td><p>71</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>August 2015</p></td><td><p>108</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>September 2015</p></td><td><p>1221</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>October 2015</p></td><td><p>925</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>November 2015</p></td><td><p>871</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>December 2015</p></td><td><p>2371</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The total is about 1.6% of all decisions Concentrix made in the same period.</p><p> </p><p>As of 15 January 2016, there are 566 mandatory reconsiderations in progress that have been opened and Concentrix are waiting for customers to provide further evidence. Concentrix have 30 further mandatory reconsiderations that are awaiting determination.</p><p> </p><p>The average length of time taken between Concentrix starting to work a mandatory reconsideration and making a decision is 24 days. This includes the time needed for customers to provide any further evidence.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","22572 ; 22668","2016-02-03T09:57:24.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444925/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444925/answer",,,,,"h