"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444933","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-01-19","<p>Information on the ages of rough sleepers is not collected centrally.</p><p>We will increase central investment over the next four years to £139 million for innovative programmes to prevent and reduce homelessness and rough sleeping. We have also protected homelessness prevention funding for local authorities, through the provisional local government finance settlement totalling £315 million by 2019/20.</p><br /><br />","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","22592","2016-01-19T16:30:36.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444933/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444933/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444933/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-01-14","Sleeping Rough: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate he has made of the number of people under the age of (a) 16 and (b) 18 sleeping rough in Greater Manchester in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","22591"
