"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445049","Leader of the House","false","2016-01-25","<p>The Office of the Leader of the House of Commons does not directly manage any buildings.</p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling",,"2016-01-25T12:34:34.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445049/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445049/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445049/answer",,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2016-01-14","Leader of the House of Commons: Defibrillators","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, how many defibrillators are provided in each building his Office manages.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","22564"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445050","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-01-21","<p>My Department is based at two locations; one in Belfast and one in London. There is no defibrillator on site in Belfast. The London office is situated in a building which is shared between several Government departments and there are 10 defibrillators on site.</p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2016-01-21T15:52:19.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445050/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445050/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445050/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-01-14","Northern Ireland Office: Defibrillators","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many defibrillators are provided in each building her Department manages.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","22565"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445051","Cabinet Office","false","2016-01-20","<p>One defibrillator has been provided in each of three buildings managed by the Cabinet Office. The buildings are: 10 Downing Street; Rosebery Court, Norwich; and Emergency Planning College, York.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","22551","2016-01-20T13:47:35.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445051/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445051/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445051/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-01-14","Prime Minister: Defibrillators","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many defibrillators are provided in 10 Downing Street.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","22566"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445052","Scotland Office","false","2016-01-20","<p>The Scotland Office manages two buildings. Dover House in London and Melville Crescent in Edinburgh. There is one defibrillator at Melville Crescent. There is no defibrillator at Dover House.</p><br />","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2016-01-20T16:19:11.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445052/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445052/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445052/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-01-14","Scotland Office: Defibrillators","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many defibrillators are provided in each building his Department manages.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","22567"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445053","Scotland Office","false","2016-01-20","<p>These figures were published by UCAS on 30 January 2015. The relevant publication can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.ucas.com/sites/default/files/january_application_rates_2015_final_0.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.ucas.com/sites/default/files/january_application_rates_2015_final_0.pdf</a></p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2016-01-20T16:22:32.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445053/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445053/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445053/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-01-14","Higher Education: Applications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, pursuant to his oral contribution of 6 January 2016, Official Report, column 275, what the source is of the figures which he quoted on application rates for higher education.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","22597"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445054","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-19","<p>Southeastern have Key Route Strategies in place in case of a line closure. These include options such as replacement buses, ticket acceptance on other routes and if possible on other forms of transport.</p><br /><p>Where events are likely to disrupt the service longer term, Southeastern consider re-working the timetable to minimise disruption as much as possible.</p><p>Southeastern work closely with Network Rail in managing such events. Network Rail and Southeastern have confirmed that whilst rail lines in the South East are extremely busy and tend to already run at capacity at peak times, it may sometimes be possible to provide extra capacity by strengthening the service on adjacent lines, depending on both rolling stock availability and operating capacity in the peak.</p><br /><p>Network Rail support train operators in providing timely information to passengers. Arrangements for putting contingency timetables in place have been improved significantly in recent years, which enables National Rail Enquiry Service to be amended earlier and more timely information to be communicated to passengers. This helps particularly with communicating timetable changes and rail replacement services.</p><br />","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-01-19T15:41:42.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445054/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445054/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445054/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-14","Southeastern","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether Southeastern trains and Network Rail have contingency plans in the event of a rail line being closed due to unforeseen circumstances in order to (a) minimise disruption to other rail lines, (b) provide extra capacity on adjacent lines to get passengers as close as possible to their usual destinations and (c) ensure that up-to-the-minute information is provided to passengers regarding alternative routes and replacement services; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Clive Efford","Eltham","Clive Efford","22575"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445055","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-19","<p>I am glad to inform the House that Network Rail re-opened the Bexleyheath line on the morning of 15 January following the landslide that temporarily closed the line.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-01-19T15:49:40.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445055/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445055/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445055/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-14","Bexleyheath Railway Line: Landslips","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he expects repairs to the Bexleyheath line to be completed; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Clive Efford","Eltham","Clive Efford","22576"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445056","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-19","<p>This is an operational matter for Network Rail. Network Rail advises that its railway earthwork assets are inspected by suitably qualified engineers at intervals of 1, 3, 5 and 10 years. The frequency of inspection is driven by the hazard rating of the asset, which is calculated from data that is recorded during visual observations across the slope.</p><br /><p>The likelihood of an earthwork asset failing increases during periods of rainfall, in particular during extreme rainfall events. During times where there is an increased likelihood of failure, additional inspections are undertaken. These are focussed with available resources on locations of highest safety risk, where the consequence of a failure is greatest.</p><br />","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-01-19T15:57:03.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445056/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445056/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445056/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-14","Railways: Landslips","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether railway verges are surveyed to identify locations where there is a danger that landslides may occur; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Clive Efford","Eltham","Clive Efford","22577"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445057","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-21","<p>I and my officials have met with industry representatives to discuss the issue of disruptive passengers on a number of occasions in recent months. In these meetings we have encouraged the industry to work towards improved data collection on incident occurrence. This will help to ensure that both industry and government have a full picture of both the scale and nature of this issue.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-01-21T16:23:30.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445057/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445057/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445057/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-14","Aviation: Antisocial Behaviour","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what work his Department has undertaken on helping develop a common reporting standard and collection method for incidents of disruptive passengers on flights departing from or arriving in the UK.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","22610"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445058","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-19","<p>The Department for Transport does not hold detailed information on the network capability and capacity of the stations on the HS1 network. HS1 Ltd, as the infrastructure manager, is responsible for producing the timetable for the line of route, within the technical and operational capability of the network. HS1 Ltd can be contacted at:</p><p>HS1 Ltd</p><p>12<sup>th</sup> Floor, One Euston Square</p><p>40 Melton Street</p><p>London</p><p>NW1 2FD</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-01-19T16:13:30.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445058/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445058/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445058/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-14","Stratford Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the maximum number is of (a) trains and (b) international trains which are able to stop at Stratford International station in each hour.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","22617"
