xceptional Hardship Scheme (EHS) </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total number of unsuccessful applications (of which were reapplications)</strong></p></td><td><p>8 (1)</p></td><td><p>31 (5)*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Unsuccessful for reasons including criterion 1 (Property Type)</strong></p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Unsuccesful for reasons including criterion 2 (Location of property)</strong></p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>18</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Unsuccesful for reasons including criterion 3 (Effort to Sell and impact of blight)</strong></p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>23</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Unsuccesful for reasons including criterion 4 (No prior knowledge)</strong></p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Unsuccesful for reasons including criterion 5 (NTS-Compelling reason to sell/EHS- Exceptional Hardship)</strong></p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>25</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>*of the five rejected reapplications none are from the same applicant.</p><br />","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-01-19T16:02:38.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445059/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445059/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445059/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-14","High Speed 2 Railway Line: Chesham and Amersham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many applications for the High Speed 2 (a) need to sell scheme and (b) exceptional hardship scheme have been received from constituents in Chesham and Amersham constituency; how many of those applications have been completed with the property now in the ownership of the Government or HS2 Ltd; how many of those properties in the ownership of the Government or HS2 Ltd have been (i) sold, (ii) rented and (iii) remain vacant; for how many of those applications that have been accepted the price has not been agreed; how many of those applications are awaiting a decision on whether they will be accepted; how many of those applications have been rejected; and of those rejected how many times each such application has been rejected and for what reasons.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","22639"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445060","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-21","<p>The current waiting time for a vocational, LGV or PCV test at Watnall test centre is 11 weeks.</p><p><br>The Driver and Vehicle and Standards Agency (DVSA) is working hard to reduce waiting times. It is recruiting for driving examiners across the UK and has specifically targeted high-wait areas. Watnall was targeted in a recent recruitment campaign DVSA launched. Once new examiners are in place in Watnall, DVSA is confident waiting times will reduce. In the meantime, DVSA is continuing to monitor waiting times closely, deploying examiners from low-wait centres and offering weekend testing wherever possible. <br></p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-01-21T15:25:56.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445060/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445060/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445060/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-14","Buses: Driving Tests","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the current waiting time is for a PCV driving examination at Watnall test centre; what steps his Department is taking to reduce that waiting time; and when he expects that waiting time to be reduced.","false","Biography information for Mr Graham Allen","Nottingham North","Mr Graham Allen","22628"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445061","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-21","<p>The Government welcomes industry’s commitment to tackling the issue of excessive alcohol consumption in airports and on-board aircraft. The use of tamper-proof bags for duty-free purchases is currently being trialled at a number of UK airports and as part of that trial industry will reach a view on the potential merits of this approach.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-01-21T16:27:01.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445061/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445061/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445061/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-14","Aviation: Alcoholic Drinks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of the use of sealed tamper-proof bags for duty-free purchases to discourage consumption of alcohol in airports or onboard aircraft in order to reduce disruptive behaviour on flights.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","22614"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445062","Home Office","false","2016-01-20","<p>Under the Licensing Act 2003, airside bars and restaurants at airports designated by the secretary of state do not require a licence. There are no plans to review this.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2016-01-20T14:49:06.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445062/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445062/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445062/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-01-14","Airports: Alcoholic Drinks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans she has to review the licensing arrangements for airside bars and restaurants in airports.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","22615"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445063","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-21","<p>There are 15 defibrillators provided in the buildings managed by the Department for Transport.</p><br />","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-01-21T16:32:59.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445063/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445063/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445063/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-14","Department for Transport: Defibrillators","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many defibrillators are provided in each building his Department manages.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","22568"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445064","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-21","<p>Information on the facilities available at individual stations is collected and held by the Association of Train Operating Companies, rather than the Department. However, we understand that around 460 stations in the UK have step free access to and between all platforms. I also note that both railway stations in the Hon Member’s constituency – Wakefield Westgate and Wakefield Kirkgate – are now step free.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-01-21T15:48:32.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445064/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445064/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445064/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-14","Railway Stations: Access","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many and what proportion of UK railway stations have steps but no lift access.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","22546"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445065","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-19","<p>This Department for Transport does not routinely collect the information requested. However, we understand that on 12 January 2016 around 11 Southeastern trains were delayed by up to 10 minutes for this reason.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-01-19T15:34:15.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445065/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445065/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445065/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-14","Railways: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many trains were reported as delayed due to winter sunlight since 4 January 2016; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Clive Efford","Eltham","Clive Efford","22573"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445066","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-19","<p>Network Rail have informed me that heavy and persistent rainfall caused the landslip.</p><br />","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-01-19T15:37:32.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445066/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445066/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445066/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-14","Bexleyheath Railway Line: Landslips","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what explanation he has received for the cause of recent landslides on the Bexleyheath rail line; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Clive Efford","Eltham","Clive Efford","22574"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445067","Wales Office","false","2016-01-22","<p>The Wales Office does not have any defibrillators in its London and Cardiff Offices.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2016-01-22T11:24:18.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445067/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445067/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445067/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-01-14","Wales Office: Defibrillators","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how many defibrillators are provided in each building his Department manages.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","22570"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445068","Women and Equalities","false","2016-01-22","<p>The Government Equalities Office (GEO) does not manage any buildings. The GEO shares premises with the Department for Education. We refer the Honourable Member for Brigg and Goole to the answer submitted by that department to PQ Number 22555.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2016-01-22T08:57:11.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445068/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445068/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445068/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2016-01-14","Government Equalities Office: Defibrillators","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, how many defibrillators are provided in each building the Government Equalities Office manages.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","22559"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445069","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-22","<p>The Department for Work and Pensions explored the option of a smaller client facing office as part of the business case.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-22T14:28:49.62Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445069/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445069/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445069/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-14","Jobcentres: Wallasey","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether he has made an assessment of the potential merits of Jobcentre Plus operating a smaller client facing office within Liscard Town Centre.","false","Biography information for Ms Angela Eagle","Wallasey","Ms Angela Eagle","22548"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445070","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-22","<p>Staff currently based at Wallasey Jobcentre Plus live in various locations throughout Merseyside. Travel considerations form an integral part of the One-to-One discussion process with all staff.</p><p>No staff will be made redundant as a result of the proposed relocation of services to Birkenhead if Wallasey Jobcentre Plus were to be closed.</p><p>There are 116 staff based at Dominick House, all of whom will be transferred to either Brunswick House or other locations depending on personal circumstances – should the closure go ahead.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-22T13:52:06.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445070/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445070/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445070/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-14","Jobcentres: Wallasey","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many staff who work at Wallasey Jobcentre Plus in Liscard live within two miles of that office; and how many of those staff will be (a) made redundant and (b) transferred as a result of the closure of that office.","false","Biography information for Ms Angela Eagle","Wallasey","Ms Angela Eagle","22547"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445071","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-22","<p>The Department does not currently hold a record of sites that have defibrillators. The Department’s current policy is not to install defibrillators on its sites unless approached by an Ambulance Trust or other external organisations who want to do so. We are, however, currently reviewing this policy to ensure it reflects up to date advice from our Occupational Health Advisers.</p><br />","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-22T11:07:36.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445071/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445071/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445071/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-14","Department for Work and Pensions: Defibrillators","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many defibrillators are provided in each building his Department manages.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","22571"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445072","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-22","<p>The Work and Health innovation fund will be used to build an evidence base for what works to improve employment and health outcomes.</p><p>This evidence base will enable the Work and Health Unit to develop proposals for Longer Term reform across Work and health Systems The Unit is currently working with partners including NHS England to develop these proposals.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-22T11:14:38.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445072/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445072/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445072/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-14","Health and Work Innovation Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what projects his Department plans to fund through the £40 million allocated to the Health and Work Innovation Fund.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","22584"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445073","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-21","<p>The Department does not routinely publish funding allocations. However, Fit for Work has been provided with sufficient funding to meet its demands for 2015/16, this financial year. Outturn spending will be detailed in DWP’s published Annual Report and Accounts.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-01-21T10:15:27.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445073/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445073/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445073/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-14","Fit for Work Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what funding his Department has allocated for the expansion of the Fit for Work service; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","22585"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445074","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-19","<p>The proposed relocation of Department for Work and Pensions colleagues from Wallasey Dominick House to Birkenhead Brunswick House will provide an expected net financial saving of around £450,000 by 2018.</p><br /><p>Notification of the 4-week consultation period was sent to all key stakeholders of Wallasey Jobcentre Plus, including Angela Eagle MP, Eric Robinson (Chief Executive Wirral Council), People Plus (Work Programme Provider), Ingeus (Work Programme Provider), Citizens Advice Bureau, and Wirral Welfare Rights.</p><br /><p>The Department has no plans to publish the outcome of the consultation.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","22580 ; 22581","2016-01-19T16:54:07.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445074/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445074/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445074/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-14","Jobcentres: Wallasey","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the savings accrued by the closure of the Wallasey Jobcentre Plus in Liscard.","false","Biography information for Ms Angela Eagle","Wallasey","Ms Angela Eagle","22579"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445075","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-19","<p>The proposed relocation of Department for Work and Pensions colleagues from Wallasey Dominick House to Birkenhead Brunswick House will provide an expected net financial saving of around £450,000 by 2018.</p><br /><p>Notification of the 4-week consultation period was sent to all key stakeholders of Wallasey Jobcentre Plus, including Angela Eagle MP, Eric Robinson (Chief Executive Wirral Council), People Plus (Work Programme Provider), Ingeus (Work Programme Provider), Citizens Advice Bureau, and Wirral Welfare Rights.</p><br /><p>The Department has no plans to publish the outcome of the consultation.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","22579 ; 22581","2016-01-19T16:54:07.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445075/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445075/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445075/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-14","Jobcentres: Wallasey","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, who his Department consulted prior to 18 September 2015 on the proposed closure of Wallasey Jobcentre Plus; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ms Angela Eagle","Wallasey","Ms Angela Eagle","22580"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445076","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-19","<p>The proposed relocation of Department for Work and Pensions colleagues from Wallasey Dominick House to Birkenhead Brunswick House will provide an expected net financial saving of around £450,000 by 2018.</p><br /><p>Notification of the 4-week consultation period was sent to all key stakeholders of Wallasey Jobcentre Plus, including Angela Eagle MP, Eric Robinson (Chief Executive Wirral Council), People Plus (Work Programme Provider), Ingeus (Work Programme Provider), Citizens Advice Bureau, and Wirral Welfare Rights.</p><br /><p>The Department has no plans to publish the outcome of the consultation.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","22579 ; 22580","2016-01-19T16:54:07.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445076/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445076/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445076/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-14","Jobcentres: Wallasey","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to his Answer of 9 September 2015 to Question 9059, which other key stakeholders have been consulted on co-locating with Wallasey Jobcentre Plus; and when he plans to publish the outcomes, responses and findings of those consultations.","false","Biography information for Ms Angela Eagle","Wallasey","Ms Angela Eagle","22581"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445077","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-20","<p>The latest statistics indicate that the majority of existing Universal Credit claimants are not yet in work.</p><p>As such they will not see a change in entitlement as a result of the April 2016 changes.</p><br />","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-20T16:20:58.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445077/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445077/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445077/answer","Witham","Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445077/answer/previousversion/39989","Biography information for Priti Patel","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-14","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answers of 11 January 2015 to Questions 21337 and 21336, what the evidential basis is for the statement that the vast majority of existing universal credit claimants will see no change in entitlement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","22516"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445078","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-19","<p>We do not retain statistics to identify the information requested, however we have safeguards in place to ensure an effective transition in these instances to avoid overlapping benefits.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-19T14:43:37.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445078/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445078/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445078/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-14","Universal Credit: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many potential overlapping payments between those processed through the universal credit live service and those processed for housing benefit have been identified in the East London Jobcentre Plus district since 2013.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","22641"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445079","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-20","<p>The information requested can only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-01-20T10:14:50.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445079/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445079/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445079/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-14","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many personal independence payment claimants were asked to attend reassessments earlier than the date originally given in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","22645"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445080","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-20","<p>Benefit is always awarded on the basis that the level of need at the start of the award will continue at the same level throughout the period of the award. In most cases the length of award is based on an intervention date decided by the decision maker, and informed by a healthcare professional.</p><br /><p>Where a claimant’s circumstances change or doubt arises as to the correctness of the award, the claimant or the department can instigate a review of that award before the planned end date. Where this happens the claimant may be asked to attend a face to face consultation with a Health Professional.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-01-20T10:24:23.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445080/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445080/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445080/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-14","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, in what circumstances claimants of personal independence payment may be asked to attend reassessments at an earlier date than initially expected.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","22646"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445081","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-19","<p>We have interpreted the question as asking how many women in total were affected by State Pension age equalisation in either the Pensions Act 1995 or the Pensions Act 2011 or the increase in the State Pension age to 66 in the Pensions Act 2011.</p><p>The estimated number of women born between April 1950 and December 1959 who are affected by the changes to State Pension age made in the 1995 and 2011 Pensions Acts is 3.48 million. This figure, rounded to the nearest 10,000, is for Great Britain and is based on DWP calculations using ONS statistics.</p><p /> <br />","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-01-19T17:47:56.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445081/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445081/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445081/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-14","State Retirement Pensions: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate his Department has made of the number of women born in the 1950s who have been affected by the changes to pension terms made in 1995 and 2011; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","22675"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445082","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-19","<p>The contractors who were commissioned to undertake the report into the evaluation of the Removal of the Spare Room Subsidy provided the Department with the final version of the report on 8 December 2015.</p><br /><p>It was agreed within the Department on 11 December 2015 and publication details were announced on the same day.</p><br />","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-01-19T11:58:41.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445082/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445082/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445082/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-14","Housing Benefit: Social Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when the final version of the Evaluation of Removal of the Spare Room Subsidy was agreed within his Department.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","22618"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445083","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-19","<p>For Working Age a total of 430,160 customersreceived their Christmas Bonus with their benefit payment for the period covering week commencing 7th December.</p><br /><p>The Pension Service has deemed that to provide a response to this PQ for any of their products could only be provided at a disproportionate cost to the Department.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-19T14:53:10.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445083/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445083/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445083/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-14","Christmas Bonus","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people were paid their Christmas bonus on their benefits in the first week of December 2015.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","22619"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445084","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-19","<p>Local Council Tax reduction schemes are delivered by Local Authorities.</p><p>Universal Credit claimants are signposted to the Local Authority for information on eligibility.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-19T14:45:29.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445084/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445084/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445084/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-14","Universal Credit: Council Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what advice his Department gives to universal credit applicants on their eligibility for council tax reduction.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","22616"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445085","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-28","<p><strong></strong></p><br /><p>The Government does not yet have any information on the take up of Statutory Shared Parental Pay. Information for the 2015-16 tax year will be available from May 2016, although it will also include claims for Additional Statutory Paternity Pay. Information is not held on the number of claims for Statutory Shared Parental Pay that are linked to adoption leave.</p><br /><p><strong></strong></p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","22624 ; 22625","2016-01-28T17:40:41.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445085/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445085/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445085/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-14","Parental Pay: Adoption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many claims for statutory shared parental pay have been linked to adoption leave since 1 April 2015.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Reynolds","Stalybridge and Hyde","Jonathan Reynolds","22621"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445086","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-20","<p>The impact of the work allowance change cannot be considered in isolation – it is part of a broader package of measures announced at the Summer Budget, such as the increase to the personal tax allowance and introduction of the national living wage.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-20T16:17:11.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445086/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445086/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445086/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-14","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if his Department will publish an impact assessment in respect of the Universal Credit (Work Allowance) Amendment Regulations 2015.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","22612"
